{
  "texts": [
    "Whether you pay attention to something to the right degree is a separate question from whether you attend to it through the right sort of psychological process, for instance.",
    "Finally, the reasons for which you attend as you do are morally assessable independently of all these considerations.",
    "Thus, we propose four distinct (primary) dimensions along which attention allocation can be morally better or worse: (1) which things one attends to; (2) how much one attends to different things; (3) the kind of attention one gives them; and (4) why one allocates one's attention this way.",
    "To illustrate how each of these dimensions matters independently, consider a well-worn case.",
    "You see a small child struggling in shallow water."
  ]
}